      <section eId="sec_140_30">
        <num>140.30</num>
        <heading>Arrest without a warrant; by any person; when and where authorized</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_140_30__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>for a felony when the latter has in fact\ncommitted such felony, and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_140_30__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>for any offense when the latter has in\nfact committed such offense in his presence.\n  2.  Such an arrest, if for a felony, may be made anywhere in the\nstate.  If the arrest is for an offense other than a felony, it may be\nmade only in the county in which such offense was committed.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
